PHASE 1 — REPLACE VERCEL BLOB WITH SUPABASE (full persistence)
================================================================

GOAL: Every piece of user state persists to Supabase, loads on app mount, 
and survives refresh / device switch. localStorage becomes an offline cache only.

1. Install + remove
   - Remove: @vercel/blob
   - Add: @supabase/supabase-js
   - Update vercel.json env block accordingly

2. Env vars (add to .env, .env.example, and README)
   - VITE_SUPABASE_URL
   - VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY

3. Create src/lib/supabase/client.ts
   - Export a singleton Supabase client
   - Throw a clear error at startup if env vars missing

4. Schema — generate a single SQL file at supabase/schema.sql I can paste into 
   the Supabase SQL editor. Include:
   - users_profile (id uuid pk = auth.uid(), created_at)
   - chat_sessions (id, user_id fk, title, created_at, updated_at)
   - chat_messages (id, session_id fk, role check in ('user','assistant'), 
     content text, tokens_in int, tokens_out int, created_at)
   - quiz_results (id, user_id, topic, difficulty, score int, total int, 
     percentage int, topics_failed text[], created_at)
   - quiz_questions_archive (id, quiz_result_id fk, question, options jsonb, 
     correct_answer int, user_answer int, explanation, topic, difficulty, was_correct bool)
   - topic_progress (id, user_id, topic, attempts int, correct int, last_review timestamptz)
   - notes (id, user_id, topic, content, created_at)
   - saved_equations (user_id, equation_id, saved_at — composite pk)
   - user_preferences (user_id pk, dark_mode bool, last_category text, last_quiz_topic text, last_quiz_difficulty text)
   - RLS enabled on every table with policies "user can only see/modify their own rows"
   - Indexes on user_id and created_at where appropriate

5. Auth
   - Add anonymous auth via supabase.auth.signInAnonymously() on first load
   - Persist the resulting session — Supabase handles this by default but verify
   - Expose useAuth() hook in src/lib/supabase/useAuth.ts that returns { userId, loading }
   - Block app render until auth resolves (show a small splash)

6. Replace src/lib/storage/blobStorage.ts with src/lib/storage/supabaseStorage.ts
   Required functions (all async, all typed, all wrapped in try/catch with 
   localStorage fallback writes for offline resilience):
   - loadAllUserData(userId) — single fetch, returns full UserData shape
   - saveChatMessage(sessionId, message)
   - createChatSession(title) -> sessionId
   - listChatSessions(userId)
   - loadChatMessages(sessionId)
   - addQuizResult(result, questions[]) — writes both quiz_results and quiz_questions_archive
   - loadQuizHistory(userId, limit?)
   - updateTopicProgress(userId, topic, correct)
   - getProgressStats(userId) — same return shape as current getProgressStats
   - addNote / deleteNote / listNotes
   - toggleSavedEquation / listSavedEquations
   - getPreferences / updatePreferences

7. Wire it up
   - MainLayout: on mount, await loadAllUserData and hydrate state
   - MainLayout: dark mode toggle now writes to user_preferences (and localStorage as cache)
   - MainLayout: when sending a chat message, persist BOTH user message and 
     assistant response to chat_messages (assistant message saved on stream completion)
   - Quiz finish: save full quiz + every question/answer to quiz_questions_archive
   - Resources panel: read live stats from Supabase (not just session counts)

8. Migration helper
   - Add src/lib/storage/migrateFromLocalStorage.ts that on first authenticated 
     load checks for the old "sie-tutor-data" localStorage key, pushes its 
     contents to Supabase, then deletes the key

